public.description:
Amore Florals, based in Leighton Buzzard, was founded in 2019 by the wonderful Miranda. With over ten years floristry experience under her belt, including time working for world-famous florist, Paula Pryke, Miranda's stunning floral designs speak for themselves.

Amore Florals believe that wedding flowers play a significant part in creating the atmosphere on the day and are guaranteed to make your big day one to remember! If you're organising a corporate event, their team can create floral designs to make sure you leave a lasting impression on your guests.

With experience working for some of London's most prestigious luxury events and celebrity weddings, Amore Florals are the perfect pick for your event. Book them here on Feast It!

Grace and Thorn is a rule-breaking florist renowned for their off-beat approach to floral and plant styling. Founded in 2011 by Nikola Southern, with the ethos that no two should ever be the same, their floral arrangements are sure to make a statement at any event. 

Grace have a extensive experience in both floral and plant design, and come armed with a plethora of vases, pots and props options for you to choose from. 

Whatever the brief, Grace and Thorn can offer small and large scale events service, weddings flowers, online and in-store bespoke bouquets and workshops too.

With regular mentions in the press, including being named top florist in London, best bouquet alongside Nikola Southern and being featured in numerous publications you can be confident that Grace and Thorn will deliver nothing but pure excellence. 

Book them on Feast It today!

The Edie rose style is natural & off-beat with a strong focus on creating stunning floral displays which are wild and free. Colours & textures which delight the eye play an important part in their style. They work with fresh, dried, preserved or faux flowers & foliage creating beautiful floral designs using seasonal flowers

From vision to completion, they offer their technical know how and work alongside you to achieve outstanding designs. With each brief they consider fresh sustainable ideas which will suit each individual client. Edie Rose strives to be as eco-friendly as possible and look for fresh innovative ways to make a difference in the industry.

Edie Rose started in 2015, when founder Helen wanted to produce beautiful floral designs which made the heart smile. They first started delivering bouquets remotely and gradually building their client base. 

Soon, they grew in size and opened 3 more shops in London to look after the day to day offerings. They then moved into the wedding and events space and started with large scale event, venues, brands & event teams across the UK.

I studied Fine Art at Lancaster University, before aspiring to abstract art for a brief time. Soon after I realised my love for flowers which led me to retrain and start my own business as an independent florist.

As a former abstract painter, my style is driven by my love for colour and composition. For me, the apogee of this can be found in an English garden, which inspires my work.

My designs harness a close eye for detail, a respect for the natural world and an appreciation of the aesthetic. From a studio space on the border of Essex and East London, I provided exquisite, elegant and romantic flowers for weddings, events, homes and businesses across the UK.

In homage to all things sustainable, I've been growing my own blooms. My cutting garden is used in tandem with seasonal flowers sourced from England’s best flower markets and local growers. In each design my aim is for you to feel my love affair with nature, the flowers provided have been tended to, hand-grown, and handpicked just for you.

At Sweet Pea Rosa we provide beautiful bespoke flowers for all occasions, creating romantic timeless bridal bouquets, stunning table centrepieces and show stopping focal florals. Based in Walthamstow, East London and founded by me, Sally, Sweet Pea Rosa brings to events over 7 years experience in floristry and an extreme passion for all things floral. The Sweet Pea Rosa style is free and natural, selecting floral recipes with complimenting colours and fragrance.

Whether you would like beautiful flowers for your wedding, party or any other special occasion, we will work with your theme and ideas to create something elegant and stylish that will compliment your day perfectly.

Flowers can transform a space from bland to grand and that's what the Floribundi team love most - surpassing expectations with their creations.

Floribundi are an independent florist based in South Bucks whose dedication to providing an outstanding service and quality product to each event has won them several awards, including Best Wedding Florist 2018 for South Bucks at the Global Wedding Awards. Every event the team work on is given the bespoke care and attention needed to ensure the big day fits your vision, with the team on hand to consult and use their creative expertise to curate beautiful floral arrangements with you.

With an expansive list of past clients, Floribundi have provided exceptional floristry for intimate dinners all the way through to large corporate do's and events for thousands. Whatever the event they always have the same mission: to take the brief and bring it to life in flowers - creativity is their middle name! 

Book Floribundi for your next event on Feast It!

Bunch London was created for a love for flowers.

After training at Scarlet and Violet and with a background in running events, Anna setup Bunch London from a Peckham studio in 2016. Long time friend and fellow florist Thomas, also with a background in production and running high end events, joined in 2017 and the duo have been creating beautiful flowers ever since. 

Be it bouquets, workshops, events or weddings, Bunch London strives to create the perfect flower for every occasion, delivered with impeccable customer service. Our dedication and eye to detail has enabled us to work with countless wonderful couples and incredible brands including; Harrods, Van Cleef & Arpels, Nyetimber, Skandium, Treatwell, LASSCO, Victor & Rolf Fragrances, Debenhams, Fellowstead & Dora Larsen Lingerie. 

Bunch is here to help you express your love for those around you and as a small business we are able to give our time and expertise to each and every client. Feel free to enquire with us right here on Feast It.

Whether it’s a wedding, private party, supper club, press launch, or birthday, Me and My Bloomers take great delight in working with you to create and design unique flowers for your event whatever the size.

They have many years of experience working on luxury events, and promise to provide an extremely professional service. Their designs tend to be influenced by the seasons, regularly taking inspiration from the English garden and countryside, embracing a more loose and natural style.

Drawing from their backgrounds in fine art, set design and event coordination, Me and My Bloomers have the ability to see your whole event, ensuring the floral design compliments every detail you have planned for your special day.

tags.name: Featured on The Big Flower Fight

public.description:
London-based Sunflowers Florist is run by the talented and passionate Raymond, star of Netflix series The Big Flower Fight. With 13 years experience under his belt in weddings, corporate and hotel floral designs, it’s no wonder Raymond won the ‘Best in Bloom’ title on episode 2 of the show!

For your wedding, Raymond and the Sunflowers Florist team can create breathtaking table centrepieces, flower arches, ceiling and stair installations as well as stunning bouquets and boutonnieres for the perfect final touch to the bridal party. Never settling for prepackaged floral arrangements, Raymond will create your floral designs from scratch to match your specific theme or Pinterest inspiration!

Looking to decorate your private or corporate party? There’s nothing Raymond can’t create from flowers and plants, including unique topiary designs from plants and moss in the shapes of animals - imagine that as a talking piece!

Sarah fell in love with flowers and studied floristry in New Zealand. She now has oodles of experience in designing truly beautiful floral creations. Her distinct styles of floristry will reflect and enhance the feel of your day, in exactly the way you want it to be remembered.

From wedding buttonholes to bridal bouquets, church flowers to table decorations, sophisticated style to colour explosions, Sarah can do it all. Although she specialises in weddings, Sarah also creates stunning floral displays for funerals, private parties and corporate events. 

Based in Hitchin, Sarah is perfectly situated for events in Hertfordshire, London and beyond and looks forward to hearing more about your event!
